WAY: 1

Create a server in a VM (either AWS or Azure).

Install Terraform on the VM.

Sign in to your cloud account from within the VM.

Create a Terraform folder in the VM.

Create the respective configuration files.

Run the Terraform commands.

Check the status directly in the cloud console.

Architecture We Will Create:
Resource Group
   ├── VNet
   │     └── Subnet
   ├── Public IP
   ├── NSG (Port 22, 80, 8080)
   ├── NIC
   └── Linux VM (Ubuntu)


WAY: 2
Write Terraform Code
        ↓
Push to GitHub
        ↓
Azure DevOps Pipeline triggers
        ↓
Terraform Init
        ↓
Terraform Plan
        ↓
Terraform Apply
        ↓
Azure Infrastructure Created


